commit.message:
fix: Handle XGetClassHint() failures

`XGetClassHint()` will not initialize passed in `hint` structure, if the
call fails.  Accessing `hint.res_name` and `hint.res_class` when
`XGetClassHint()` failed accesses random memory.

Also, refactored `add_icon` error handing a bit.  Hopefully, it is
easier to read in this form.  As there are a few cases when `classname`
would be unnecessary, I've moved `classname` initialization to be after
those are checked.

Check /usr/share/xsl/docbook for DOCBOOK_ROOT

Fixes compilation on Void Linux where docbook-xsl is installed at
/usr/share/xsl/docbook

cli: 'grow_gravity' => 'grow-gravity'

CLI arguments use dash as word separator.  'grow-gravity' style was
accidentally changed in

commit c3c99c0b0672594a5d286728a665139e28ad38bb
Author: d3adb5 <me@d3adb5.net>
Date:   Fri May 19 17:01:08 2023 -0700

    refactor: let parameters accept argc and argv (#27)
cli: Enforce required short form arguments

chore: make ignore_classes exclusive to the rc file

Make it so classes can only be ignored through stalonetray's resource
configuration file, as the setting now takes multiple arguments for the
class names instead of a single, comma-separated one.

feat: accept arguments as class names in ignore-classes

Accept using arguments as class names instead of tokenizing a single
string of comma-separated class names.

fix: allow unlimited arguments

Actually check the value of max_argc for parameters before comparing the
given arguments to the maximum allowed number. This way a zero value for
max_argc actually does allow unlimited arguments.
Fix documentation typo

refactor: let parameters accept argc and argv (#27)

Let parameters accept an argument count and array of argument values
instead of a single argument. The parameter struct has been changed to
allow a range of argument counts instead of the previous, takes &
is_optional implementation.
